CSC173 has the course title "Computation and Formal Systems". CSC173 is a 4.0 credit course taught by George Ferguson. CSC173 is offered every "Summer Spring Fall ". Investigation of several formal systems influential in computer science, and also some of their applications (e.g. inspiring and providing the foundation for a computer programming style, or providing the basis for solving important practical problems like communications protocols, compiling, systems analysis, graphics ...) This course is available to majors only during the registration period. Prerequisites: CSC172 and MATH150.